Canva Layout Plan (Left-to-Right Flow)

⸻

1️⃣ Box 1 — Input

Title: 🟦 Multilingual Doctor–Patient Dialogue
Subtitle: “Conversations in English, Hindi, Gujarati, Tamil, Telugu, etc.”
Color: Light blue (#A7C7E7)
Icon suggestion: 💬 Speech bubble or stethoscope
Arrow → to Box 2

⸻

2️⃣ Box 2 — Tokenization / Preprocessing

Title: 🟧 Tokenizer + Preprocessing
Subtitle: “Unicode normalization, truncation (≤32k tokens), language tagging”
Color: Light orange (#F7C880)
Icon: ⚙️ small gear
Arrow → to Box 3

⸻

3️⃣ Box 3 — Stage 1: Summary Generation

Title: 🟩 Stage 1: English Summary Generation
Subtitle: “LoRA-tuned Qwen generates concise English summary”
Example (small text below box):
‘Doctor advised CT scan for throat discomfort.’
Color: Light green (#A8E6A1)
Icon: 📄 document symbol
Arrow → to Box 4

⸻

4️⃣ Box 4 — Stage 2: JSON Extraction

Title: 🟨 Stage 2: Field-by-Field JSON Extraction
Subtitle: “Each schema field predicted as a Q–A pair”
Example (tiny text below box):
Q: What is the diagnosis? → A: Laryngitis.
Color: Light yellow (#FFF3B0)
Icon: {} or 🗂️ database symbol
Arrow → to Box 5

⸻

5️⃣ Box 5 — Stage 3: Multilingual Q&A

Title: 🟥 Stage 3: Multilingual Q&A Response
Subtitle: “Answers generated in input’s original language”
Example:
Q: रोगी की मुख्य शिकायत क्या है? A: गले में खराश।
Color: Light red (#F6A6A6)
Icon: 💬 Chat bubble
Arrow → to Box 6

⸻

6️⃣ Box 6 — Final Outputs

Title: 🟪 Final Outputs
Subtitle:
	1.	English Summary
	2.	Structured JSON
	3.	Multilingual Q&A
Color: Lavender (#CBB2FE)
Icon: 📊 or grouped file symbols
Arrow → None (final output)

⸻

🧩 Suggested Layout Settings (in Canva)
	•	Flow Direction: Left to right (horizontal)
	•	Box shape: Rounded rectangles (consistent corner radius)
	•	Arrow type: Solid arrows (medium thickness)
	•	Spacing: Equal distance between boxes
	•	Text alignment: Center (Title bold, Subtitle regular, Example italic)
	•	Font pairing:
	•	Title: Montserrat Bold (11–12 pt)
	•	Subtitle: Open Sans Regular (9–10 pt)
	•	Example (italic): Roboto Italic (8 pt)

⸻

✨ Optional Footer Text (below the diagram)

Pipeline executed independently for each language with checkpoint resumption and LoRA-tuned inference for factual accuracy.
